newsitem.title: UK: NWE gasoline prices dip with crude, demand limited.
newsitem.headline: NWE gasoline prices dip with crude, demand limited.

text.p: NWE spot gasoline prices eased back in late trade as crude gave up early gains. But tight Rotterdam supplies cushioned losses, traders said.
Eurograde gasoline barges traded at $223 asnd $221.50 fob ARA in the morning, $6 up from Monday's highest trade, but levels dipped back to hover around $220-$221 in late business.
Dealers said buying interest was very thin at these levels and limited mainly to essential short-covering only.
Despite reports of extremely tight Rotterdam avails, many traders considered the recent gains overdone when compared to the limited demand in NWE and narrow arbitrage options.
